```python
def return_n_smallest_chars(string):
    string = sorted(string)
    chars_list = []
    for i in range(80):
        chars_list.append(string[i])
    return chars_list
```
Note: This function presumes that the input string will have at least 80 distinct characters. Also, in Python `sorted` will sort characters by their ASCII values.
